attributes.Long form description: In the first step, the instructor asks to switch the Joy-con from the pad to the hand help grip. The student disassembles the Joy-cons, takes the hand help grip, mounts the Joy-con on the hand help grip. In the second step, the instructor asks to switch the Joy-con's from the hand help grip to the straps. The student disassembles the joy-con, the student takes the straps and mounts them on the controls, the instructor indicates that he/she mounted the straps backwards and asks the student to correct this action. The student takes the controls again and mounts them correctly on the straps. The instructor indicates that he forgot to place the strap locks. The student puts on the strap locks correctly. In the third step, the instructor instructs the student to switch the controls back to the console pad. The student disassembles the red Joy-con, removes the strap lock, disassembles the strap control and mounts it on the pad, takes the blue control, mounts it on the console pad.  In the fourth step, the instructor asks the student to open the kickstand and place the console on the table. Take the console, flip the console over and lift the kickstand, place the Nintendo Switch on the table. In the fifth step, the instructor asks you to change the game card. Open the game slot, press the game card, remove the game card and put it on the table, take the new game card, insert the card into the game slot, close the game slot cover.  In the sixth step, the instructor asks to replace the SD card. The student turns the console over and inspects where the SD card slot is located. He removes the SD card, places it on the table, takes the new SD card and inserts it into the console. Step 7, the instructor asks the student to turn on the console. The student lightly inspects the console and presses the top button, waits for the Nintendo Switch to turn on completely.  Eighth step, the instructor asks the student to turn off the console. The student holds down the top button and presses the corresponding option on the touch screen.  The instructor thanks and asks to end the recording.
